Package: cakechart
Title: Rectangular Alternatives to Pie Charts
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Isaac", "Faber", , email = "isaac@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Pie charts are hard to interpret because humans struggle to compare
    angles and arc lengths. The 'cakechart' package provides rectangular
    alternatives — "cake charts" — that subdivide a rectangle into proportional
    slices. This plays to human strengths at comparing lengths and positions along
    a common scale. Works both standalone via cake_chart() and as a 'ggplot2'
    extension via geom_cake().
